🧠 PART 3: TRICKY FOLLOW-UP QUESTIONS
🧠 Q: Why is cache faster than RAM?

👉
Because cache is closer to CPU and uses faster memory (SRAM), reducing access time.

🧠 Q: Why deadlock is dangerous?

👉
Because processes remain stuck forever and system resources are wasted.

🧠 Q: Why paging is better than segmentation?

👉
Because it avoids external fragmentation and simplifies memory management.

